		<item>
		<title>Update: Marking of Expiry Date on H20</title>
		<link>https://www.cmhammar.com/update-marking-of-expiry-date-on-h20/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mikael Lundholm]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 15 Aug 2024 08:28:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Bulletin]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.cmhammar.com/?p=10056</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Manufacturer&#8217;s instruction for the marking of Expiry Date on H20 HRU is updated from &#8220;Markings must be done solely by a manufacturer of liferafts or an authorised liferaft service station.&#8221; to &#8220;Expiry Date must be marked on the H20 prior to installation onboard&#8221; The update is in force with the update to MED Certificate 07493/G0...</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/update-marking-of-expiry-date-on-h20/">Update: Marking of Expiry Date on H20</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com">Hammar</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Manufacturer&#8217;s instruction for the marking of Expiry Date on H20 HRU is updated from &#8220;Markings must be done solely by a manufacturer of liferafts or an authorised liferaft service station.&#8221; to &#8220;Expiry Date must be marked on the H20 prior to installation onboard&#8221;</p>
<p>The update is in force with the update to MED Certificate <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/07493_G0-MED.pdf">07493/G0</a> and H20 Manual <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/KOM-3085-v.2.0-H20-Manual-HT-0019_11.05.pdf">v11.05</a></p>
<p>For any questions regarding this update, please get in touch with Technical Sales.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/update-marking-of-expiry-date-on-h20/">Update: Marking of Expiry Date on H20</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com">Hammar</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
